Open a terminal and navigate to the directory where you saved the file
---> on top off visual studio click Terminal 
        ---> New terminal
        ---> cd Desktop
        ---> cd Tictactoe
        ---> node tictactoe.js

The game will prompt you to make moves by specifying the row and column (both ranging from 0 to 2). For example:


Player X, enter row (0-2): 1
Player X, enter column (0-2): 2
The game board will be displayed after each move. If a player wins or the game ends in a tie, the result will be shown, and the program will exit.

Follow the prompts until the game concludes.

Follow the steps to final game results

